As a noun:\n\n\nObject: The object of the sentence is the thing that the verb is acting upon. For example, in the sentence \"She picked up the object,\" the object is the thing she picked up.\n\n\n2. As a pronoun:\n\n\nObject: The object of a pronoun is the noun or pronoun that the pronoun replaces. As an adjective:\n\n\nObject: The object of an adjective is the noun or pronoun that the adjective modifies.
